explanation: This solution uses a prime factorization approach to find the minimum number of operations. It iterates from 2 to n and for each number i, it checks if n is divisible by i. If it is, it means that we can get n 'A's by copying and pasting i times, so we add i to the result and divide n by i. This approach is efficient because it only needs to iterate up to the square root of n, and it uses constant space.

